{\par \b Syntax:}\par CHOOSE(var, \u8220?title\u8221?, \u8220?item1\u8221?, \u8220?item2\u8221?,[\u8230?&quot;item14&quot;]) or CHOOSE(var,&quot;title&quot;,\{&quot;item1&quot;...&quot;itemN&quot;)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Displays a choose box with the given title and containing items with the strings &quot;item1&quot;, etc. If the user choose an object, var will be updated to contain the number of the selected object (an integer, 1, 2, 3, \u8230?); otherwise, stores zero in var if the user exits without choosing.\par \par Returns true (non zero) if the user selects an object, otherwise return false (0).\par
